# Project: Radio Udaan

**Workspace**: `/Users/nexus/Documents/Radio Udan`

## Tech Stack
| Layer | Technology |
|----|-----|
| Mobile | Flutter (Android + iOS) |
| Backend/Admin | WordPress + Forminator (free) |
| App API | Custom WP plugin (“App API”) exposing REST endpoints |
| Auth | OTP (India), provider abstraction (MSG91 default; switchable) |

## Non-negotiables (must not change)
- **All registrations happen inside the app** (app-first).
- **One Forminator form per event** in WordPress (strict 1:1 mapping).
- App renders **dynamic form schemas** from the WP App API to minimize app updates.

## Architecture (high level)
- WP holds event content + Forminator forms.
- Custom WP plugin exposes:
  - events list/details
  - per-event dynamic form schema (derived from Forminator)
  - registration submission (stores entries; tags `source=app`)
  - uploads endpoint (with server-driven constraints)
  - OTP request/verify façade
- Flutter app consumes API, renders schema-driven registration forms, and submits registrations in-app.

## Key Product Rules
- **One form per event**: each event is linked to a single Forminator form ID.
- Every registration entry must be tagged with **`source=app`** (and optionally `source=web` later).
- Upload constraints (types/sizes/count) should be **configurable in WP admin**, not hardcoded in the app.

## Data source of truth
- **Live WordPress DB** from `radio-udan-wordpresss-website/wp-config.php` — not `nexusfle_radio.sql` (archived dump only).

## Store compliance (mandatory)
- Read `.cursor/memory/store-compliance.md` before Flutter work and store releases.
- No `READ_SMS` on Android; manual OTP only. No Sign in with Apple unless social logins added.
- In-app account deletion, Privacy Policy link, YouTube embed (stream only, no download), background audio for radio.

## Risk Areas to watch
- OTP abuse/rate limiting and identity/session model
- File upload abuse and PII handling (UDID cards, audio/video)
- Logging/monitoring without leaking PII
- Accessibility quality (TalkBack/VoiceOver) as a release blocker

